extends _layout.pug
block content
  include _header.pug

  main.wrapper.wrapper--no-bottom
    section#intro
      p Request header parser is yet another small API built for #[a(href='https://learn.freecodecamp.org/apis-and-microservices/apis-and-microservices-projects/request-header-parser-microservice', target='_blank') freeCodeCamp]. The app attempts to discover the IP address, preferred languages and system infos of the user.

    section#user-stories
      h3 User Stories
      p We only have one user story this time.
      blockquote
        ul.stories
          li.stories__item <input class="stories__checkbox" type="checkbox" checked disabled> I can get the IP address, preferred languages (from header <code>Accept-Language</code>) and system infos (from header <code>User-Agent</code>) for my device.

    section#usage
      h3 Example Usage
      p You can use the <code>/api/whoami</code> endpoint or click that huge button below to fetch the data from the API.

      .row
        .col
          button.btn.btn--large#test Click to Test the API
        .col
          textarea.form__field#output(placeholder='API response will be displayed here...', rows=5, disabled)

    section#notes
      p The example above uses the #[a(href='https://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/Web/API/Fetch_API', target='_blank') fetch() API] to get the results via AJAX requests. It works in all modern browsers (Chrome 42+, FireFox 39+, Safari 10+, Opera 29+, and Edge 14+ only); IE is not supported.
      p The live preview won't work for you in Internet Explorer or really old browsers; however, you can still try the API by opening the <a href="api/whoami"><code>/api/whoami</code></a> endpoint directly.
      p The GitHub repo is available here: #[a(href='https://github.com/zsoltime/fcc-api-request-header') Request Header Parser Microservice]

  include _footer.pug
  script(src='app.js')
